{
  "title": "RenderNodePass",
  "description": "Renders a scene subtree (a RenderNode) as one pass — into the active target, or off-screen when `options.target` is set. The most common pass: world, HUD overlay, an off-screen scene capture. `view`/`target`/`clear` are fixed at construction; only `enabled`/`label` are mutable. The off-screen redirect is built once and reused every frame (no per-frame allocation). The node and any caller `target` are NOT owned by this pass — `destroy()` never frees them.",
